node.text:
Thank you to all the growers out there running our 645w LED Pro. We've had tremendous success with our first LED product. It taught us a lot as well as our growers in how to use LED technology correctly.⠀
⠀
Luxx Lighting was founded on the development of improved HPS and CMH fixtures and now we are taking the next step in LED technology.⠀
⠀
R&D on new LED technology resulted in lots of failures along the way. With each failure we learned. With failure comes opportunity. ⠀
⠀
We are dropping some new LED products this fall which are the results of our learnings along the past year of testing LEDs with some of the best cultivators in the world. ⠀
⠀
#LuxxLighting #ByGrowersForGrowers

node.text:
@phatpanda @javematters Stacking the 645w LED closer than a 4x4 footprint. We haven't seen anyone running a lighting array closer than these guys, straight crush mode on Grape Cream Cake. ⠀
⠀
35 lights in this room with 13 tons of cooling and 4, 205-pint dehumidifiers.⠀
⠀
Running at 60% on the start date and transitioned to 100% within 7 days at 18” from the top of the canopy. "The largest benefit we have found was of course the increased PPFD output. This room was originally equipped with 24 1000w HPS fixtures that averaged around 600 ppfd. After the switch, our average ppfd is now around 900 and we are still saving on energy consumption. In addition to this, the finished product is simply incredible. We are seeing the same, if not better performance than our standard HPS program." - Tyler, Facilities Manager @thctech1791⠀and Mojave, AG Director @javematters 
⠀
#LuxxLighting #PhatPanda #ByGrowersForGrowers

PPFD footprint testing is a huge part of our R&D at Luxx Lighting. We use this testing to maintain quality control and to establish benchmarks to make improvements. We test dozens of prototype fixtures, along with fixtures from most of our competitors. It starts in our testing room constructed out of DPS panels to simulate the most realistic reflectance parameters. We test in a 5.5' x 14' wide room which lets us test up to 3 lights in an array, and get a good look at overlap. We collect 33 test points on a 4' x 4' footprint and 41 test points on a 5' x 5' footprint using a Gigahertz-Optik CSS-45 meter. Testing heights range from 6" to 4'. ⠀
⠀
#LuxxLighting #ByGrowersForGrowers

node.text:
@standardflower in Detroit going all in on LED, 2nd run running full rooms of our 645w LED Pro’s after swapping out their Gavita DE’s and pulling 59 lbs. off of 23 lights on their first run.

“For the last 10 years I have been a cultivator in the beautiful state of Michigan. I operate 3 warehouses, each ones a little different than the other. I noticed a wave in LED lights coming through and people swearing by them one by one. 

Me being the person I am always leery of new technology for the mere fact that the old LEDs from back in the day never really worked well. For the price you pay, not worth it when it came down to the yield, quality, output, etc. So when I did my research on these new LEDs I still wasn’t convinced but decided to try out the 645w LED Pro in one of my rooms.

That happened to be the best yield as well as quality product I’ve ever had. I never believed the 1.9 grams per watt until it was physically in my face. The best part about it I never took the lights to 100%, never had to. 

My plants are thanking me, my electric bill and air conditioners are thanking me and my customers are thanking me. 

I now switched all of my facilities to 645w LED Pro’s and recommend them to all my family and friends. THESE GUYS ROCK from the product to the support."

#LuxxLighting #ByGrowersForGrowers
